 Here is an example of how you can represent this information as a JSON object:

```json
{
    "people": [
        {
            "name": "Mark",
            "gender": "male",
            "age": 19
        },
        {
            "name": "Joe",
            "gender": "male",
            "age": 19
        },
        {
            "name": "Sam",
            "gender": "female",
            "age": 30
        }
    ]
}
```
This JSON object contains an array of objects, each representing a person. Each person has three properties: `name`, `gender`, and `age`. The values for these properties are defined according to your specification (Mark and Joe are males who are 19 years old, while Sam is a female who is 30 years old).
